theorem
Th23: (for K being  Fanoian Field holds ((perm2 is  even iff ( sgn (perm2,K) ) = ( 1_ K )) & (perm2 is  odd iff ( sgn (perm2,K) ) = ( - ( 1_ K ) ))))
proof
set n2 = ( n + 2 );
let K being  Fanoian Field;
A1: ( len ( Permutations n2 ) ) = n2 by MATRIX_2:18;
thus A2: (perm2 is  even implies ( sgn (perm2,K) ) = ( 1_ K ))
proof
assume perm2 is  even;
then (ex L being (FinSequence of ( Group_of_Perm n2 )) st ((( ( len L ) mod 2 ) = ( 0 ) & perm2 = ( Product L )) & (for i holds (i in ( dom L ) implies (ex q2 st (( L . i ) = q2 & q2 is  being_transposition)))))) by A1,MATRIX_2:def 12;
hence thesis by CKB24:1;
end;

thus (( sgn (perm2,K) ) = ( 1_ K ) implies perm2 is  even)
proof
assume A3: ( sgn (perm2,K) ) = ( 1_ K );
consider P being (FinSequence of ( Group_of_Perm n2 )) such that A4: perm2 = ( Product P ) and A5: (for i holds (i in ( dom P ) implies (ex trans being (Element of ( Permutations n2 )) st (( P . i ) = trans & trans is  being_transposition)))) by CKB30:1;
assume perm2 is  odd;
then ( ( len P ) mod 2 ) <> ( 0 ) by A1,A4,A5,MATRIX_2:def 12;
then ( ( len P ) mod 2 ) = 1 by NAT_D:12;
then ( sgn (perm2,K) ) = ( - ( 1_ K ) ) by A4,A5,CKB24:1;
hence thesis by A3,CKB31:1;
end;

hence thesis by A2,CKB19:1,CKB31:1;
